The engine uses three cross-domain discovery mechanisms. Embedding cosine similarity (0.5-0.92 window) pairs semantically related nodes [K1]. Partition bridges allow cross-domain pairing between otherwise isolated domains [K2]. Abstract patterns tag nodes with structural analogies that embeddings miss [K5]. Quality gates filter output structurally but don't assess intellectual quality [K3]. Salience decay promotes fresh content while breakthrough floors preserve validated insights [K4].